1
00:00:02,603 --> 00:00:04,397
<i>All we want to do
is help our patients,</i>

2
00:00:04,421 --> 00:00:06,032
<i>but what they don't teach
us in medical school is:</i>

3
00:00:06,056 --> 00:00:07,084
there are so many
ways to do harm.

4
00:00:07,108 --> 00:00:09,074
<i>Previously on</i> The Resident...

5
00:00:10,094 --> 00:00:12,022
- The surgery was canceled.
- They can't do that.

6
00:00:12,046 --> 00:00:13,078
Yes, they can.

7
00:00:13,113 --> 00:00:14,975
<i>Is your pride really worth more</i>

8
00:00:14,999 --> 00:00:15,980
<i>than the life of a patient?</i>

9
00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:18,217
Chief of Surgery. Resident.

10
00:00:18,252 --> 00:00:19,852
Try to remember that.

11
00:00:19,887 --> 00:00:22,187
You don't have the
right to play God, Conrad.

12
00:00:22,222 --> 00:00:25,057
There's always art
balanced with science.

13
00:00:25,092 --> 00:00:28,010
<i>- You okay?
- Just worried about him.</i>

14
00:00:28,045 --> 00:00:29,856
Fortunately, I happen
to be Rembrandt.

15
00:00:29,880 --> 00:00:33,699
I think Lane's overtreating
her patients, including Lily.

16
00:00:33,734 --> 00:00:34,944
We have to do
something about Lane.

17
00:00:34,968 --> 00:00:38,202
We're gonna find out
what it is. Together.

18
00:00:38,238 --> 00:00:41,406
We need to have a
physician running Chastain.

19
00:00:41,441 --> 00:00:44,426
The CEO will see you now.

20
00:00:56,873 --> 00:00:58,840
Guess who's on a break?

21
00:00:58,876 --> 00:01:01,509
- Me.
- Yeah, you and me.

22
00:01:01,544 --> 00:01:03,678
Chastain can take
care of itself right now.

23
00:01:03,714 --> 00:01:05,591
Our downtime is
finally synced up.

24
00:01:05,615 --> 00:01:07,448
It has been a while.

25
00:01:07,484 --> 00:01:10,268
Patients are fine,
a quick page away,

26
00:01:10,304 --> 00:01:12,738
which is why I've
taken it upon myself

27
00:01:12,773 --> 00:01:14,773
to acquire these beauties.

28
00:01:14,808 --> 00:01:16,258
In the interest of time...

29
00:01:16,293 --> 00:01:17,904
Our chief resident,
Dr. Benjamin,

30
00:01:17,928 --> 00:01:19,472
is at a medical
convention in Denver.

31
00:01:19,496 --> 00:01:20,929
These keys are to his office.

32
00:01:20,964 --> 00:01:22,281
With a sofa and a locking door?

33
00:01:22,316 --> 00:01:23,765
A shower and a locking door.

34
00:01:29,139 --> 00:01:31,089
♪ Buy yourself a dream ♪

35
00:01:31,124 --> 00:01:33,391
♪ How's it looking? ♪

36
00:01:33,427 --> 00:01:34,593
♪ Buy yourself a car ♪

37
00:01:34,628 --> 00:01:36,728
♪ And a house to live in ♪

38
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:40,298
♪ Get yourself a girl ♪

39
00:01:40,334 --> 00:01:43,168
♪ Someone different,
buy yourself a dream ♪

40
00:01:44,705 --> 00:01:46,254
♪ And it won't mean nothing... ♪

41
00:01:46,289 --> 00:01:48,456
Just leave it.

42
00:01:48,492 --> 00:01:50,737
Damn it.

43
00:01:53,130 --> 00:01:55,329
Mine or yours?

44
00:01:55,365 --> 00:01:57,282
Mine.

45
00:02:00,354 --> 00:02:02,571
911.

46
00:02:02,606 --> 00:02:05,073
♪ It all could be different ♪

47
00:02:05,108 --> 00:02:07,025
♪ Time to do something new ♪

48
00:02:07,061 --> 00:02:08,610
♪ I've given everything ♪

49
00:02:08,662 --> 00:02:12,113
♪ I want to be a
happy man, too. ♪

50
00:02:23,660 --> 00:02:25,043
Secret admirer?

51
00:02:25,078 --> 00:02:27,328
Someone's getting jealous?

52
00:02:27,363 --> 00:02:29,381
They're for you,

53
00:02:29,416 --> 00:02:30,960
but Phoebe in the flower
shop does have eyes for me.

54
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:33,151
I may have flirted
my way to a discount.

55
00:02:33,186 --> 00:02:35,153
- Phoebe, huh?
- Yeah.

56
00:02:35,188 --> 00:02:36,805
Half Asian girl with...

57
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:39,140
High-pitched voice,
drenched in perfume.

58
00:02:39,175 --> 00:02:41,659
I know Phoebe, and...

59
00:02:41,695 --> 00:02:46,064
I admire her work, but
this was unnecessary.

60
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:48,984
Well, my perfectly
stitched heart begs to differ.

61
00:02:51,705 --> 00:02:53,004
Can you stay?

62
00:02:59,179 --> 00:03:01,296
I wish I could,
but I have a case.

63
00:03:01,331 --> 00:03:03,081
Newborn,

64
00:03:03,116 --> 00:03:05,851
<i>sick heart the size of a walnut.</i>

65
00:03:05,886 --> 00:03:08,736
<i>We have to reroute blood
flow so she can get oxygen.</i>

66
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:10,872
<i>She's extremely high risk.</i>

67
00:03:23,287 --> 00:03:25,236
What are her odds?

68
00:03:25,271 --> 00:03:27,250
Part of Mabel's heart
is underdeveloped.

69
00:03:27,274 --> 00:03:30,325
The defect is more
severe than we thought.

70
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:32,727
Without surgery, two days tops.

71
00:03:32,780 --> 00:03:36,047
With surgery,
she's got a real shot.

72
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:38,266
Yeah, a long shot.

73
00:03:38,302 --> 00:03:41,052
Mr. Thoms, your wife
brought these beautiful twins

74
00:03:41,087 --> 00:03:42,904
into this world together.

75
00:03:42,939 --> 00:03:45,101
It is my mission to reunite
them in a few hours,

76
00:03:45,125 --> 00:03:47,025
and I am not in a losing mood.

77
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,410
Rarely am I.

78
00:03:50,714 --> 00:03:52,431
I feel dizzy.

79
00:03:52,466 --> 00:03:53,948
Hey, stay calm.

80
00:03:53,983 --> 00:03:57,585
Okay? Just stay calm. Stay cool.

81
00:03:57,638 --> 00:04:01,456
Your pulse is ridiculously
high. Look at me.

82
00:04:01,492 --> 00:04:04,142
We can't have you stroking
out before I bring Mabel back

83
00:04:04,178 --> 00:04:06,111
to her brother
Matt, you hear me?

84
00:04:06,146 --> 00:04:07,824
- Help is on the way.
- Yeah.

85
00:04:07,848 --> 00:04:09,448
- Let's go.
- Okay.

86
00:04:14,004 --> 00:04:15,748
<i>Today,</i>

87
00:04:15,772 --> 00:04:18,139
a once-prominent
Atlanta oncologist,

88
00:04:18,175 --> 00:04:21,126
Dr. Lane Hunter, was arraigned
on one charge of murder

89
00:04:21,161 --> 00:04:25,058
and 12 charges of insurance
fraud and money laundering.

90
00:04:25,082 --> 00:04:28,399
Dr. Hunter is accused
of fraud and murder.

91
00:04:28,435 --> 00:04:32,154
She provided false medical
information to cancer patients

92
00:04:32,189 --> 00:04:34,250
in order to charge them
thousands of dollars

93
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:36,675
in unnecessary chemotherapy.

94
00:04:36,710 --> 00:04:37,943
Did you take a shower?

95
00:04:37,978 --> 00:04:39,927
Don't worry about it.

96
00:04:39,963 --> 00:04:41,512
Where did you take a shower?

97
00:04:41,548 --> 00:04:45,801
Mr. Thoms,
Dr. Hawkins, this is Dr...

98
00:04:45,836 --> 00:04:48,519
Pravesh. We met in the
ER when my wife came in.

99
00:04:48,555 --> 00:04:50,149
- How's she doing?
- She's resting.

100
00:04:50,173 --> 00:04:52,740
And I'm gonna head back down
shortly again and check on her.

101
00:04:52,776 --> 00:04:54,804
We stopped by to make
sure you're feeling okay.

102
00:04:54,828 --> 00:04:56,594
BP a little high?

103
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:57,962
Have a seat.

104
00:05:00,984 --> 00:05:02,934
Any palpitations?

105
00:05:02,970 --> 00:05:05,953
My baby girl's in the OR,

106
00:05:05,989 --> 00:05:09,691
my baby boy won't stop crying,
labor almost killed my wife.

107
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:11,604
Now she's in the ICU.

108
00:05:11,628 --> 00:05:13,545
Yes. Palpitations.

109
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:17,865
BP's 180/120.

110
00:05:17,901 --> 00:05:19,695
Normal protocol would
be to send you down

111
00:05:19,719 --> 00:05:21,186
to the ER for observation.

112
00:05:21,221 --> 00:05:23,338
There's no way in
hell I'm leaving my son.

113
00:05:23,373 --> 00:05:24,867
Oh, we get it,

114
00:05:24,891 --> 00:05:26,286
but there's a rule

115
00:05:26,310 --> 00:05:28,454
against dads having
heart attacks in the NICU.

116
00:05:28,478 --> 00:05:31,646
Let us run some labs,
get an EKG, start you

117
00:05:31,699 --> 00:05:33,509
on some blood pressure meds,
make sure that doesn't happen.

118
00:05:33,533 --> 00:05:36,067
What do you say?

119
00:05:36,102 --> 00:05:38,386
- Okay.
- Yeah?

120
00:05:38,422 --> 00:05:40,016
- Okay.
- All right.

121
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:42,908
Um, I want to
check in on my wife.

122
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:52,066
Dr. Pravesh.

123
00:05:52,102 --> 00:05:54,836
Melanie. Welcome back.

124
00:05:54,871 --> 00:05:56,588
You gave us quite a scare.

125
00:05:56,623 --> 00:05:58,823
You lost a lot of
blood during delivery.

126
00:05:58,859 --> 00:06:00,191
How are you feeling?

127
00:06:00,227 --> 00:06:03,010
How are my babies? Mabel?

128
00:06:03,046 --> 00:06:06,747
As you know, Mabel has
hypoplastic left heart syndrome.

129
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:09,050
Prenatal imaging can
only tell us so much,

130
00:06:09,085 --> 00:06:11,752
so we didn't know the
severity of her heart deformity

131
00:06:11,788 --> 00:06:14,573
- until she was born.
- Is she okay?

132
00:06:14,608 --> 00:06:17,375
I haven't even met her yet.

133
00:06:19,112 --> 00:06:21,780
<i>Soon after birth, she
was taken into surgery,</i>

134
00:06:21,815 --> 00:06:24,899
<i>but I assure you that she is
in the best possible hands.</i>

135
00:06:38,315 --> 00:06:40,248
<i>Dr. Sharavino</i>

136
00:06:40,283 --> 00:06:43,051
called and said you're having
another flare? What's going on?

137
00:06:43,086 --> 00:06:45,971
Oh, fever, body
aches, yeah, the usual.

138
00:06:46,006 --> 00:06:48,372
Our mom also had lupus,
which led to kidney failure,

139
00:06:48,408 --> 00:06:50,141
and then she died,

140
00:06:50,176 --> 00:06:52,694
so "the usual" can
be fatal in our family.

141
00:06:52,729 --> 00:06:54,707
Well, we'll be extra careful.

142
00:06:54,731 --> 00:06:56,714
Any, um, sore
throat, congestion?

143
00:06:56,749 --> 00:06:58,299
Peeing a lot, a little pain.

144
00:06:58,335 --> 00:07:00,163
Okay, well, we'll definitely
run your blood work,

145
00:07:00,187 --> 00:07:01,552
but if it's anything like

146
00:07:01,587 --> 00:07:02,998
your last three
admissions, it'll be a UTI,

147
00:07:03,022 --> 00:07:05,941
so we'll get you started
on doxycycline to make sure

148
00:07:05,976 --> 00:07:07,971
it doesn't turn into
a kidney infection.

149
00:07:07,995 --> 00:07:09,977
Oh, she has a mild allergy to...

150
00:07:10,013 --> 00:07:12,158
To doxycycline. An antihistamine
should help head off the hives

151
00:07:12,182 --> 00:07:13,582
you got on your last visit.

152
00:07:13,617 --> 00:07:15,667
Um, will a doctor
be in soon or...?

153
00:07:15,702 --> 00:07:18,085
I'll be back shortly.

154
00:07:18,138 --> 00:07:20,683
- Can you get off that thing for,
like, a second?
- I would,

155
00:07:20,707 --> 00:07:22,988
but it's way more interesting
than you are right now.

156
00:07:24,194 --> 00:07:26,010
Run this blood work. Thanks.

157
00:07:29,999 --> 00:07:32,383
Hot, hot, hot, hot!

158
00:07:39,142 --> 00:07:41,259
NEWSWOMAN: <i>Legal experts note</i>

159
00:07:41,295 --> 00:07:44,412
that if Dr. Hunter were
found guilty, she may face

160
00:07:44,448 --> 00:07:46,114
the death...

161
00:07:57,911 --> 00:08:00,231
We need some help!

162
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,974
Bypass.

163
00:08:25,154 --> 00:08:27,238
Scalpel.

164
00:08:27,274 --> 00:08:29,407
Thank you.

165
00:08:29,442 --> 00:08:31,425
Ready for this?

166
00:08:33,714 --> 00:08:35,046
And here...

167
00:08:35,081 --> 00:08:38,065
we go.

168
00:08:56,937 --> 00:08:59,370
♪ ♪

169
00:09:15,538 --> 00:09:17,739
Will Matt be okay? And Mabel?

170
00:09:17,774 --> 00:09:19,758
Is she-is she in surgery?

171
00:09:19,793 --> 00:09:22,176
Do they have power? Is
she okay? What's happening

172
00:09:22,211 --> 00:09:24,590
- with Mabel?
- Mabel's with the best surgeons
I know.

173
00:09:24,614 --> 00:09:26,113
Matt will be fine.

174
00:09:26,148 --> 00:09:28,599
What about these other
babies? Are they all right?

175
00:09:28,635 --> 00:09:30,018
It's gonna be fine. Stay calm.

176
00:09:30,053 --> 00:09:33,555
I got this.

177
00:09:33,590 --> 00:09:35,940
Stopped crying. Why
isn't he crying anymore?

178
00:09:35,976 --> 00:09:39,010
Get me an Ambu bag.

179
00:09:55,244 --> 00:09:57,545
He could have died.
What is going on?

180
00:09:57,580 --> 00:09:59,380
The power went out.

181
00:09:59,415 --> 00:10:01,644
Likely due to the storm.
Backup power kicked on now.

182
00:10:01,668 --> 00:10:03,646
It's limited, but we
got emergency lights

183
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:05,330
and necessary equipment,
so we're good to go.

184
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:08,406
- You okay?
- Yeah, yeah.

185
00:10:08,442 --> 00:10:10,141
All right.

186
00:10:15,015 --> 00:10:16,775
Took too long for those
generators to come on.

187
00:10:16,799 --> 00:10:18,516
Yeah, that wasn't cool at all.

188
00:10:18,551 --> 00:10:20,580
I'm gonna go to the basement,
make sure everything's okay.

189
00:10:20,604 --> 00:10:21,986
Until full power's restored,

190
00:10:22,021 --> 00:10:24,000
revert back to
standard triage protocol.

191
00:10:24,024 --> 00:10:26,591
Put the sickest together, get
ready to evacuate if needed.

192
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:28,504
Find me if he
has a heart attack.

193
00:10:28,528 --> 00:10:29,989
<i>All right, gather around.</i>

194
00:10:30,013 --> 00:10:31,957
We're operating on
backup power now,

195
00:10:31,981 --> 00:10:34,165
so no computers,
no digital charts,

196
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,128
and the paper ones are
buried in the basement, so...

197
00:10:36,152 --> 00:10:40,805
so, write pertinent
information on each patient.

198
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:44,959
Write clearly, write
concisely, follow me.

199
00:10:44,995 --> 00:10:48,646
5920... monitor urine output.

200
00:10:48,682 --> 00:10:50,097
We need him peeing like a champ.

201
00:10:50,132 --> 00:10:53,634
5921... alcohol
withdrawal, taper diazepam.

202
00:10:53,670 --> 00:10:56,304
5918... do not
ask about the cats.

203
00:10:56,339 --> 00:10:58,055
It gives him PTSD.

204
00:10:58,090 --> 00:11:01,008
5917... check vitals every 30
minutes. Come on, keep up.

205
00:11:01,061 --> 00:11:04,062
Dr. Bell, should we deploy
emergency protocols A or B?

206
00:11:04,097 --> 00:11:06,564
Dr. Bell. Dr. Bell, all
computer systems are down.

207
00:11:06,599 --> 00:11:08,699
Dr. Bell, trauma is
completely jammed.

208
00:11:08,735 --> 00:11:10,079
Is that why you're not
taking any patients in the ER?

209
00:11:10,103 --> 00:11:12,036
Do you have a better solution?

210
00:11:12,071 --> 00:11:14,083
Dr. Bell, we're almost
at capacity down there.

211
00:11:14,107 --> 00:11:17,191
Dr. Bell, ortho has a dozen
scheduled cases. Keep or cancel?

212
00:11:17,226 --> 00:11:19,655
- Is that why you're not taking any patients
at the moment? Computer systems are down.

213
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:22,730
Mr. Bell, why is this happening?

214
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:26,134
It's Dr. Bell.

215
00:11:26,169 --> 00:11:27,930
I recommend thinking
before you speak.

216
00:11:27,954 --> 00:11:30,154
If that's too much of a
challenge, don't speak.

217
00:11:31,675 --> 00:11:33,491
There's a massive storm outside.

218
00:11:33,527 --> 00:11:35,042
The power grid is down.

219
00:11:35,077 --> 00:11:36,355
There's a team
working with the city

220
00:11:36,379 --> 00:11:38,579
to get it restored
as soon as possible.

221
00:11:38,615 --> 00:11:40,059
The fire department
is on their way to help

222
00:11:40,083 --> 00:11:41,566
with emergency power, if needed.

223
00:11:41,601 --> 00:11:44,168
Treat all current trauma
patients, then shut it down.

224
00:11:44,204 --> 00:11:46,020
ER stays open to capacity.

225
00:11:46,055 --> 00:11:47,499
Let me know the
second that happens.

226
00:11:47,523 --> 00:11:49,991
Ortho hits pause. Don't
cancel a single surgery.

227
00:11:50,026 --> 00:11:52,004
Slide 'em an hour.
When we're back up,

228
00:11:52,028 --> 00:11:54,079
start cutting. All
hands on deck.

229
00:11:54,114 --> 00:11:55,579
Focus. Communicate.

230
00:11:55,615 --> 00:11:57,409
The hospital and our
patients will be fine.

231
00:11:57,433 --> 00:11:58,950
Decisions go through me.

232
00:11:58,985 --> 00:12:00,935
Get back out there.

233
00:12:05,141 --> 00:12:06,757
Albert, why are you still here?

234
00:12:06,793 --> 00:12:08,071
In regards to the trauma center,

235
00:12:08,095 --> 00:12:09,772
I think we can
consider a better option.

236
00:12:09,796 --> 00:12:12,130
Not unless you want a
one-way ticket to Caracas

237
00:12:12,165 --> 00:12:15,099
as your last stop
on the surgical train.

238
00:12:15,134 --> 00:12:16,601
Leave.

239
00:12:21,674 --> 00:12:24,559
You know, policy dictates

240
00:12:24,594 --> 00:12:26,360
that we abandon surgery

241
00:12:26,395 --> 00:12:28,580
until full power is restored.

242
00:12:28,615 --> 00:12:30,898
Closing now is a death sentence.

243
00:12:30,951 --> 00:12:32,245
No doubt. But, legally,

244
00:12:32,269 --> 00:12:35,102
baby Mabel was
simply a sad casualty

245
00:12:35,137 --> 00:12:36,770
of unfortunate circumstances.

246
00:12:36,823 --> 00:12:39,707
What to do, what to do?

247
00:12:39,743 --> 00:12:42,109
Don't be dramatic. You
know what we're going to do.

248
00:12:42,144 --> 00:12:45,446
Oh, look who put their
big girl pants on today.

249
00:12:45,481 --> 00:12:46,998
Okafor...

250
00:12:47,033 --> 00:12:49,150
if we continue

251
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:51,002
and Mabel doesn't survive...

252
00:12:51,037 --> 00:12:52,754
Coin toss at this point...

253
00:12:52,789 --> 00:12:55,006
Are you willing to lay
your head next to mine

254
00:12:55,041 --> 00:12:56,390
