00:33:36,548 --> 00:33:38,843
Better question is why
I'm not at MIT anymore.

757
00:33:38,867 --> 00:33:42,235
Answer: hospital bills so
crippling, I had to drop out

758
00:33:42,271 --> 00:33:44,454
and she had to
declare bankruptcy.

759
00:33:46,408 --> 00:33:49,826
Are you faking
symptoms to be here?

760
00:33:49,861 --> 00:33:51,656
Look, we want less
hospital, not more...

761
00:33:51,680 --> 00:33:54,047
Why would she fake her symptoms?

762
00:33:54,082 --> 00:33:56,661
Because I think she hacked
into our system to shut us down.

763
00:33:56,685 --> 00:33:58,062
That's crazy. Joplin...

764
00:33:58,086 --> 00:33:59,319
This isn't the first time

765
00:33:59,354 --> 00:34:00,431
that someone's hacked
into our computer.

766
00:34:00,455 --> 00:34:02,505
The attacks started on July 4.

767
00:34:02,540 --> 00:34:04,090
You were here then.

768
00:34:06,561 --> 00:34:08,444
Is this true?

769
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:10,947
Did you do this?

770
00:34:10,982 --> 00:34:13,750
- Why? Why would you do...
- Are you kidding me?

771
00:34:13,785 --> 00:34:15,669
Medical bills ruined us.

772
00:34:15,704 --> 00:34:18,171
Chastain ruined us. I
can't get the job that I want

773
00:34:18,206 --> 00:34:19,522
without the degree from MIT.

774
00:34:19,558 --> 00:34:20,523
We are making it work.

775
00:34:20,559 --> 00:34:22,458
We are barely getting by.

776
00:34:22,494 --> 00:34:24,372
You're working two jobs
in order to make payments

777
00:34:24,396 --> 00:34:26,357
to Chastain for my
bill. And for what?

778
00:34:26,381 --> 00:34:27,681
So the hospital can get rich?

779
00:34:27,716 --> 00:34:30,132
Damn right I hacked
into the billing department.

780
00:34:30,168 --> 00:34:31,595
To get our lives back.
To wipe our slate clean.

781
00:34:31,619 --> 00:34:33,386
Wait, the billing department?

782
00:34:33,422 --> 00:34:35,738
No, your cyber
attack is responsible

783
00:34:35,774 --> 00:34:37,523
for this entire power outage.

784
00:34:37,559 --> 00:34:39,036
That's not possible.
The code I created

785
00:34:39,060 --> 00:34:40,071
was only to wipe out billing.

786
00:34:40,095 --> 00:34:41,595
Whatever you intended,

787
00:34:41,647 --> 00:34:43,746
it did a hell of a
lot more than that.

788
00:34:43,782 --> 00:34:45,459
You severed our
connection to the grid.

789
00:34:45,483 --> 00:34:46,867
You said that was the storm.

790
00:34:46,902 --> 00:34:48,151
We were wrong.

791
00:34:48,186 --> 00:34:50,253
Well, I-I messed up.

792
00:34:50,288 --> 00:34:51,238
- It must've rep...
- People's lives

793
00:34:51,273 --> 00:34:53,139
are in danger because of you.

794
00:34:54,109 --> 00:34:56,159
I... I-I can try to fix it.

795
00:34:56,194 --> 00:34:57,234
Let me try to fix it.

796
00:35:05,704 --> 00:35:08,638
If she can fix this, do you have
to tell anyone what happened?

797
00:35:08,673 --> 00:35:10,823
You saw the damage
her virus caused.

798
00:35:10,859 --> 00:35:13,020
Joplin's a good person
who did something stupid.

799
00:35:13,044 --> 00:35:14,761
Young people do dumb stuff.

800
00:35:14,796 --> 00:35:16,340
I hear you, but right
now let's just focus

801
00:35:16,364 --> 00:35:18,831
on getting the hospital
back up and running again.

802
00:35:18,867 --> 00:35:21,000
Look, I know I'm asking
for too much, but...

803
00:35:21,036 --> 00:35:23,854
so far, no one's
gotten hurt, right?

804
00:35:24,872 --> 00:35:26,856
We are barely
surviving as it is.

805
00:35:26,891 --> 00:35:28,959
I honestly don't know how...

806
00:35:28,994 --> 00:35:30,577
Please, I know this is bad...

807
00:35:30,612 --> 00:35:32,445
Here. Uh, i-it's a full backup

808
00:35:32,498 --> 00:35:34,375
of-of the hospital
computers I made

809
00:35:34,399 --> 00:35:36,460
before I did what I
should've never done.

810
00:35:36,484 --> 00:35:38,585
A-All hackers make 'em, in case.

811
00:35:38,620 --> 00:35:40,660
Give it to I.T. They'll
know what to do.

812
00:35:41,907 --> 00:35:44,958
I deserve whatever
happens to me, but

813
00:35:44,993 --> 00:35:46,525
Rachel didn't know anything.

814
00:35:46,561 --> 00:35:47,978
Make sure they know that.

815
00:35:48,013 --> 00:35:50,029
And that I'm sorry. I really am.

816
00:35:52,050 --> 00:35:54,000
I'll pass that on.

817
00:35:57,072 --> 00:35:59,355
God. I'm sorry.

818
00:35:59,390 --> 00:36:02,024
- Sorry...
- Don't...

819
00:36:02,060 --> 00:36:04,171
I gave the drive to I.T.
Power's being restored now.

820
00:36:04,195 --> 00:36:05,790
But Bell doesn't
need to know that yet.

821
00:36:05,814 --> 00:36:07,458
No, we're gonna
lie to help Joplin out.

822
00:36:07,482 --> 00:36:09,816
I like that way
you think. I'm in.

823
00:36:09,851 --> 00:36:13,152
We can get you the
antidote to the malware.

824
00:36:13,187 --> 00:36:15,249
The person is remorseful
and asking for leniency

825
00:36:15,273 --> 00:36:16,239
before they hand it out.

826
00:36:16,274 --> 00:36:17,523
Blackmail?

827
00:36:17,558 --> 00:36:19,025
Let's just call it negotiating.

828
00:36:19,060 --> 00:36:20,626
Well, what are we talking about?

829
00:36:20,662 --> 00:36:22,306
A nurse demanding
more mental health days?

830
00:36:22,330 --> 00:36:24,998
Some millennial intern's crusade

831
00:36:25,033 --> 00:36:26,744
for more acai bowls
in the cafeteria?

832
00:36:26,768 --> 00:36:28,162
A patient

833
00:36:28,186 --> 00:36:30,047
whose life was
destroyed by Chastain.

834
00:36:30,071 --> 00:36:31,087
And a PR nightmare.

835
00:36:31,123 --> 00:36:32,922
Don't need another one of those.

836
00:36:32,957 --> 00:36:34,235
Chastain's computers
were vulnerable.

837
00:36:34,259 --> 00:36:37,054
- Our generators
weren't up to code.
- Not my fault.

838
00:36:37,078 --> 00:36:38,939
- Press won't see it that way.
- Patients' lives

839
00:36:38,963 --> 00:36:40,775
were in jeopardy. It's
unlikely they'll put the blame

840
00:36:40,799 --> 00:36:42,365
on Charles the I.T. guy.

841
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:44,495
What is it with you two?

842
00:36:44,519 --> 00:36:46,047
Sticking your necks
out for some patient

843
00:36:46,071 --> 00:36:47,654
you just met a few hours ago.

844
00:36:47,689 --> 00:36:49,155
Seriously?

845
00:36:49,191 --> 00:36:51,241
Chastain shined during

846
00:36:51,276 --> 00:36:53,326
a crippling power
outage likely caused

847
00:36:53,362 --> 00:36:55,862
by...

848
00:36:55,897 --> 00:36:57,280
bad weather.

849
00:36:57,315 --> 00:37:00,083
And a young patient's life

850
00:37:00,118 --> 00:37:02,001
isn't completely ruined.

851
00:37:02,036 --> 00:37:05,554
That's a win-win.

852
00:37:05,590 --> 00:37:08,074
Well, nice try, but hacking
into a hospital database,

853
00:37:08,109 --> 00:37:09,709
cutting off its power,

854
00:37:09,744 --> 00:37:11,127
endangering countless lives...

855
00:37:12,631 --> 00:37:14,359
I need a name.

856
00:37:14,383 --> 00:37:16,048
We're not asking for anonymity.

857
00:37:16,083 --> 00:37:18,234
We're just asking for leniency.

858
00:37:22,007 --> 00:37:23,556
Well...

859
00:37:23,591 --> 00:37:25,386
handling this
quickly and quietly

860
00:37:25,410 --> 00:37:27,611
is in everyone's best interest.

861
00:37:27,646 --> 00:37:31,013
So, deal?

862
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,182
Yeah.

863
00:37:38,757 --> 00:37:40,623
Wait for it.

864
00:37:40,658 --> 00:37:44,077
Wait for it...

865
00:37:45,663 --> 00:37:46,763
Ah.

866
00:37:46,798 --> 00:37:48,431
And then there was light,

867
00:37:48,466 --> 00:37:51,417
and he saw that it was good.

868
00:37:54,005 --> 00:37:56,956
We saved that kid's life.

869
00:37:56,991 --> 00:37:58,558
He's gonna make it, by the way.

870
00:37:58,593 --> 00:38:00,576
You sure<i> you're</i> gonna make it?

871
00:38:00,611 --> 00:38:02,757
That improv surgery is the
craziest thing I've ever done

872
00:38:02,781 --> 00:38:05,093
in my life. I mean, I don't
know whether to thank you

873
00:38:05,117 --> 00:38:07,078
or to punch you.

874
00:38:07,102 --> 00:38:09,085
Hey, I carried a fully-grown man

875
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:10,847
up three flights
of stairs today.

876
00:38:10,871 --> 00:38:12,689
And you're telling me this why?

877
00:38:12,724 --> 00:38:14,640
Because I broke a sweat

878
00:38:14,675 --> 00:38:18,060
and you know where
there's a secret shower.

879
00:38:21,116 --> 00:38:23,111
Dr. Benjamin's office.
You earned these today.

880
00:38:23,135 --> 00:38:27,036
But... you didn't
get 'em from me.

881
00:38:27,071 --> 00:38:28,672
You have my word.

882
00:38:31,142 --> 00:38:34,026
You do know Benjamin
<i>is</i> back in the office now?

883
00:38:38,300 --> 00:38:40,633
Good.

884
00:38:43,471 --> 00:38:45,166
Uh, what happened
in the elevator

885
00:38:45,190 --> 00:38:46,639
stays in the elevator.

886
00:38:46,675 --> 00:38:50,109
Not something I'd
want to advertise.

887
00:38:50,144 --> 00:38:51,494
Right.

888
00:38:55,366 --> 00:38:56,966
Looks good.

889
00:38:58,386 --> 00:39:01,320
Make sure he takes it
easy for the next few days.

890
00:39:01,355 --> 00:39:03,656
Not sure that's how
this new-dad thing works.

891
00:39:03,691 --> 00:39:05,074
I've got my eye on him.

892
00:39:05,110 --> 00:39:06,190
I'll keep him in line.

893
00:39:07,161 --> 00:39:09,145
Uh, thank you, Dr. Pravesh.

894
00:39:09,180 --> 00:39:11,130
We can't... can't
thank you enough.

895
00:39:11,166 --> 00:39:14,400
Mr. and Mrs. Thoms, someone
here is excited to see you.

896
00:39:19,374 --> 00:39:21,540
Your daughter's a warrior.

897
00:39:21,575 --> 00:39:22,987
We repaired her heart,

898
00:39:23,011 --> 00:39:25,595
and it's even stronger
than we expected.

899
00:39:28,115 --> 00:39:29,527
How long has he been crying?

900
00:39:29,551 --> 00:39:32,035
Since they took
Mabel for surgery.

901
00:39:32,070 --> 00:39:34,020
Nothing we've tried
has calmed him.

902
00:39:40,212 --> 00:39:43,179
I have an idea.

903
00:39:43,215 --> 00:39:47,178
Until today, these
babies shared a womb.

904
00:39:47,202 --> 00:39:51,353
They don't know an existence
without the touch of the other.

905
00:39:51,389 --> 00:39:54,352
And then they were thrust
into a huge, cold world,

906
00:39:54,376 --> 00:39:56,192
alone.

907
00:39:58,212 --> 00:40:00,479
They missed each other.

908
00:40:02,133 --> 00:40:05,351
Everything's gonna be A-OK.

909
00:40:09,074 --> 00:40:10,890
I don't think it's working.

910
00:40:10,925 --> 00:40:14,610
- Give it a moment.
- ♪ You are my sunshine ♪

911
00:40:14,645 --> 00:40:19,131
♪ My only sunshine ♪

912
00:40:19,167 --> 00:40:23,119
♪ You make me happy ♪

913
00:40:23,154 --> 00:40:26,723
♪ When skies are gray ♪

914
00:40:26,758 --> 00:40:31,127
♪ You'll never know, dear ♪

915
00:40:31,162 --> 00:40:35,098
♪ How much I love you ♪

916
00:40:35,133 --> 00:40:38,083
♪ Please don't take ♪

917
00:40:38,119 --> 00:40:42,188
♪ My sunshine away ♪

918
00:40:54,803 --> 00:40:59,083
♪ The other night, dear ♪

919
00:40:59,107 --> 00:41:02,976
♪ As I lay sleeping ♪

920
00:41:03,011 --> 00:41:05,561
How's the baby?

921
00:41:06,548 --> 00:41:09,115
Resting comfortably.

922
00:41:09,150 --> 00:41:11,600
How are you?

923
00:41:11,636 --> 00:41:13,519
♪ When I awoke, dear ♪

924
00:41:13,554 --> 00:41:15,332
Feels like I'm never
getting out of here.

925
00:41:15,356 --> 00:41:20,042
♪ I was mistaken ♪

926
00:41:20,077 --> 00:41:23,479
♪ So I hung my head ♪

927
00:41:23,514 --> 00:41:26,299
♪ And I cried. ♪

928
00:41:32,724 --> 00:41:34,474
You're fired.

929
00:41:34,509 --> 00:41:35,875
What?

930
00:41:35,910 --> 00:41:37,504
- I just saved your neck.
- You risked.

931
00:41:37,528 --> 00:41:40,096
I saved. Get out.

932
00:41:41,883 --> 00:41:43,310
First thing tomorrow,
we need to...

933
00:41:43,334 --> 00:41:45,000
You're wholly incompetent.

934
00:41:45,036 --> 00:41:47,169
- Meaning?
- You're fired.

935
00:41:47,205 --> 00:41:49,672
Talk to HR about severance.

936
00:41:58,199 --> 00:42:01,300
Any available resident to ICU 3.

937
00:42:01,335 --> 00:42:03,836
Dr. Bell.

938
00:42:03,871 --> 00:42:05,722
You wanted to see me?

939
00:42:05,757 --> 00:42:07,873
Great save today.

940
00:42:07,908 --> 00:42:10,170
Thank you. You know, it's
days like this that make...

941
00:42:10,194 --> 00:42:13,495
Just cut the crap and tell me
exactly what happened in the ER.

942
00:42:13,531 --> 00:42:16,032
Who was there?

943
00:42:20,038 --> 00:42:21,271
Who made the first cut,

944
00:42:21,306 --> 00:42:23,806
you or Conrad Hawkins?

945
00:42:31,916 --> 00:42:33,094
My place?

946
00:42:33,118 --> 00:42:35,067
I don't know. I'm so tired.

947
00:42:35,102 --> 00:42:37,603
Oh, we'll be sleeping like
babies before you know it.

948
00:42:37,638 --> 00:42:38,905
That sounds amazing.

